# most important golden rules used by experienced traders 

---
 1. Protect your capital first
> “If you lose your money, you’re out of the game.”


Risk only 1–2% per trade
Always use a stop-loss
Survival > profits


---
 2. Cut losses fast, let winners run
Small losses are normal
Big losses = account killer

 Close losing trades quickly Don’t rush to take profit too early

---
 3. Never trade without a plan
Before entering, know:
Entry point
Stop-loss
Take profit

If you don’t know all 3 → don’t enter

---
 4. Patience pays more than action
Most beginners:
Trade too much
Chase every move

Pros:
Wait for clean setups only

 No setup = no trade

---
 5. Don’t chase breakouts
This links to what you learned:
Chasing = entering late
Often leads to fake breakout traps

 Wait for confirmation or retest

---
 6. Trade with the trend
Trend is your best friend
Counter-trend = harder, riskier

 Simple rule:
Uptrend → look for buys
Downtrend → look for sells


---
 7. Emotions destroy accounts
Big enemies:
Fear
Greed
Revenge trading

 Stick to your plan, not your feelings

---
 8. Journal your trades
Track:
Why you entered
What happened
Mistakes

 This is how you improve fast

---
 9. One good setup is enough
You don’t need:
10 trades a day

You need:
1–2 high-quality trades


---
 10. Confluence = probability
Don’t rely on one signal.
Combine:
Support/resistance
Trend
Volume
Price action

 More confluence = better odds

---
 11. The market owes you NOTHING
No trade is guaranteed
Losses are part of the game

 Think in probabilities, not certainties

---
 12. Consistency > big wins
One lucky trade means nothing
Repeating a solid strategy = success


---
 Simple mindset shift
Bad trader:
> “Will this trade win?”


Good trader:
> “Does this trade follow my rules?”
